  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strategic Assistance for Emergency Response in DRC - SAFER 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Consortium, led by Mercy Corps, working with Norwegian Refugee Council (NRC), ACTED, Solidarites International (SI), and Concern Worldwide, in this second phase of the SAFER programme, will continue to respond to the needs of people affected by conflict and natural disasters in Eastern DRC. This is a 12 month intervention that will provide packages of support (Multi-sectoral market based (CVA) or in-kind assistance and complementary to specific Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WaSH) ) to 561,409 displaced and or conflict affected people.</narrative>
  </description>
